FBIS4-62679 "drsov096_p_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-096 Daily Report 17 May 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Spokesman Rejects Azeri Charge on Disrupting Talks Spokesman Rejects Azeri Charge on Disrupting Talks LD1705202894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1835 GMT 17 May 94 LD1705202894 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Press-Secretary of the Armenian Foreign Ministry Aram Safaryan dismissed a statement by the Azeri side that talks on the settlement of the Karabakh problem with participation of defense ministers of Armenia, Azerbaijan and Commander of the Nagorno-Karabakh Army mediated by Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev were disrupted by Yerevan's fault. Earlier on Tuesday [17 May] a source in the Azeri Embassy in Moscow claimed that Armenia insisted on considering the status of Nagorno-Karabakh along with the withdrawal of troops from seized Azeri territories. Press-secretary of the Armenian president Levon Zurabyan declined to comment on the situation around the talks until the return of the Armenian delegation from Moscow.
